    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process of using dried palm fronds to make objects. For example, this is one of the most important and main traditional crafts in Al-Ula city, and is exclusively practiced by women. Numerous tools and products are made out of dried palm fronds to be used in housework, agriculture, and may be used in everyday life in urban zones as well. (Nasif, 1995).</Note_Text>
